{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> κατηγορ-έω</b>, <br /> <b>speak against</b>, especially before judges, <b>accuse</b>, opposed to ἀπολογέομαι, with <i>genitive</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.113, 8.60, 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 14.21, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 1073, etc.; τῆς πόλεως 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Menexenus” 244e: less frequently κατά τινος 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 1.7.9 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; κ. τινὸς πρὸς τὴν πόλιν <b>denounce</b> him publicly, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Euthyphro” 2c \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; κατηγόρεις [αὐτῶν] ὡς λέγοιεν you <b>accused</b> them of saying, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.134, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 7.1.38 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; κ. τινὸς ὅτι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\".. [prev. work] 1.7.17; τῶν ἱππέων ἐλθὼν πρὸς ὑμᾶς εἰς τὴν ἐκκλησίαν κατηγόρει 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.197; τῆς ἐμῆς [τύχης] κατηγορεῖς [prev. author] 18.266, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 3.4. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> κ. τί τινος <b>bring as a charge against</b> a person, <b>accuse</b> him <b>of</b> it, δείν᾽ ἔπη μου [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 514, compare 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Orestes” 28, etc.; τῶν ἄλλων μωρίαν 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 1.3.4; ὃς ἐμοῦ Φιλιππισμὸν κατηγορεῖ 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 18.294; κ. τι κατά τινος 4th c.BC: Hyperides Orator “pro Euxenippo” 23; τινὸς περί τινος 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 1.110, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 8.85 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>infinitive</i>, κ. τινὸς παθεῖν τι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 482c: with double _genitive_, παρανόμων κ. τινός 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.5. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> with <i>accusative</i> <i>of things</i> only, <b>allege in accusation</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.113; μωρίαν ἐμήν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Heraclidae” 418; τὴν πονηρίαν τῶν γονέων 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Protagoras” 346a; τὰ γεγονότα κ. 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 1.10, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 932, “Ra.” 996 (Lyric poetry), 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 13.31, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 19.9 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, <b>to be brought as an accusation against</b>, κατηγορεῖτο τοὐπίκλημα τοῦτό μο; [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 529; ἀδικία πολλὴ κ. αὐτοῦ 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.95 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὰ πρῶτά μου ψευδῆ -ημένα the first false <b>charges brought against</b> me, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Apologia” 18a, compare 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 16.9; τὰ -ηθέντα 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 5.85, 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 1.24; τἀδικήμαθ᾽ ἃ κατηγορεῖται 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.136: _impersonal_, followed by \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<i>infinitive</i>, σφέων.. κατηγόρητο μηδίζειν <b>a charge had been brought against</b> them that.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.205; κατηγορεῖτό τινος ὡς βαρβαρίζοι 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 5.2.35 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; κατηγορουμένου δ᾽ αὐτοῦ, ὅτι.. <b>a charge being brought against</b> him, that.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 3.5.25. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__3.b</b></Level4> rarely in <i>passive</i>, of the person, <b>to be accused</b>, οἱ κατηγορούμενοι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 1.7, compare 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Tim.” 38 (assuming variant). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> <i>absolutely</i>, <b>to be an accuser, appear as prosecutor</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 840, 842, “Pl.” 917, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Apologia” 18e, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>signify, indicate, prove</b>, c.<i>accusative</i> <i>of things</i>, [τὸ νεαρὸν] κ. τὴν ὀλιγοετίαν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 1.4.3, compare 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.695d, 4th c.AD: Adamantius Physiognomonicus 1.5, +others; ἀσθένειαν μᾶλλον ἢ δύναμιν 3rd c.AD: Plotinus Philosophus 4.6.3 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>display</b>, οἱ πολλὴν -οῦντες ἀπειροκαλίαν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Nigr.” 21: with _genitive_ _person_, εὖ γὰρ φρονοῦντος ὄμμα σοῦ κατηγορεῖ 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 271, compare 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Fragmenta” 690, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 907, etc.; ὠκύτητα κ. τοῦ κυνός 2nd-3rd c.AD: Philostratus Sophista “Philostrati majoris imagines” 2.26. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> followed by <i>relative</i>, <b>declare, assert</b>, αὐτὸ κατηγορέει τὸ οὔνομα ὡς ἔστι Ἑλληνικόν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.115 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; κ. ὅτι.. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 4.189, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 73b (_impersonal_)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>absolutely</i>, <b>make a definite assertion</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Tht.” 208b. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> in Logic, <b>predicate of</b> a person or thing, τί τινος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Categoriae” 3a19, +others, 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “Fragmenta” 250 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; κυρίως, καταχρηστικῶς κ., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Philodemus Philosophus “περὶ ποιημάτων” 5.15; ἐναντίως ὑπὲρ τῶν αὐτῶν [prev. author] “Oec.” p.60 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]: —more frequently in <i>passive</i>, <b>to be predicated of</b>.., τινος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Categoriae” 2a21, “APr.” 26b9, +others; κατά τινος [prev. author] “Cat.” 2a37; κατὰ παντὸς ἢ μηδενός [prev. author] “APr.” 24a15: less frequently ἐπί τινος [prev. author] “Metaphorical” 998b16, 999a15; so later ἐφ᾽ ἑνὸς οἴονται θεοῦ ἑκάτερον τῶν ὀνομάτων -εῖσθαι 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis 2.48; περί τινος 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Topica” 140b37; τὸ κοινῇ -ούμενον ἐπὶ πᾶσιν [prev. author] “SE” 179a8: _absolutely_, τὸ κατηγορούμενον\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] <b>the predicate</b>, opposed to τὸ ὑποκείμενον (the subject), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Cat.” 1b11, compare “Metaphorical” 1043a6, +others\">Refs</a>]; κατηγορεῖν καὶ -εῖσθαι <b>to be subject</b> and <b>predicate</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “APr.” 47b1. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.2</b></Level3> <b>affirm</b>, opposed to ἀπαρνέομαι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 41a10. \">Refs</a>] <i>adverb</i> κατηγορουμένως <b>categorically, roundly</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Philodemus Gadarensis Epigrammaticus “Ir.” p.90 W. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G2723","accentedUnicode":"κατηγορέω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G2725","matchingForm":"κατήγορος","stepTransliteration":"katēgoros","gloss":"accuser","_zh_tw_Gloss":"控告者","_es_Gloss":"acusador","_zh_Gloss":"控告者"}],"shortDef":"to accuse, bring charges against","mediumDef":"to accuse, bring charges against <br /><b>to speak against, accuse, bring charges against</b> <ref='Mat.12.10; 27:12'>Mt. 12:10; 27:12</ref>; <ref='Jhn.5.45'>Jn. 5:45</ref>","stepGloss":"to accu